pull_request.title: Add test env for Postgres SSL
pull_request.body:
Adds a docker-compose based environment for local testing of SSL-enabled Postgres.

Uses the super-useful "authority" container to handle the pain of issuing certificates (kudos @andmarios :heart: ):

https://github.com/lensesio-dev/sre-docker-imagers/tree/master/other/authority

It then generates the appropriate lenses config (using the new config implemented by https://github.com/lensesio-dev/lenses-core/pull/1205)

issue.title: Fix DTO to be run only in development mode
issue.body: DTO convention for `_SPEC_VERSION` which gets parsed from openapi file had the format `v<semantic version>` as seen [here](https://ci.lenses.io/job/lenses-ci-g2/job/backend.build/job/master/318/artifact/openapi-3a56c1220706008fb53c35f8329632994115cb84.yaml/*view*/) but currently `v` has started being [omitted](https://ci.lenses.io/job/lenses-ci-g2/job/backend.build/view/tags/job/v4.1.0-rc.2/1/artifact/openapi-f496420efc9ef4452440829310b9855304a5b2b8.yaml/*view*/) which ultimately breaks the DTO stage and job. This small fix addresses this by using regex.
